Hyram do you believe that the placement of acne can tell you what‚Äôs causing it? I don‚Äôt normally believe in pseudoscience but normally I get acne on my chin because of hormones, but this month it‚Äôs on my upper cheeks and I just looked up what it means and it says it can be caused by a lot of stress, which I have been under üòÖ but I just want to know what you think about that, does our skin really reflect our insides like that?
As a dermatology resident - no. The only correlation there really is is that adult onset hormonal acne tends to locate around the jawline, but even that is not a hard and fast rule.

I'm also from Europe, Finland specifically. LRP and Isntree aren't cheap in my opinion either when you buy them in stores here; LRP sunscreens are easily 25‚Ç¨. But ordering online Asian sunscreens can be pretty afforable. I use the EU Stylevana site and I've never had to pay any extra customs fees if the order is under 150‚Ç¨. A couple of good sunscreens I've ordered from there were the Biore Watery Gel SPF50 and Cosrx Ultra-Light Invisible SPF50. The Cosrx was my favourite out of the two. Neither of them stung or were shiny for me, but Biore does contain alcohol so keep that in mind if you're sensitive to it.
